			<ns0:name>cbiffle@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/cbiffle@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Since the recent changes to enable NaClCheckDEP, the platform_qualify library requires sel, which in turn requires platform_qualify.  This did not cause an error because platform_qualify's dependence on sel is not specified in the build files!

This is bad for two reasons:
1. Practically, this is making testing the platform_qualify library difficult.  i.e. it cannot build unless I also happen to be building sel.
2. In the abstract, circular dependencies are bad.

We should factor the signal handling out of the sel target into a separate library target.  (It could stay in the same directory -- I don't care.)  This will convert the sel-&amp;gt;PQ-&amp;gt;new_library dependence into a DAG.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-02-24T18:40:26.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-10-21T21:55:52.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Available</ns2:status><ns2:cc>
